    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@Kikobeats Not so easy to do, easiest would be to use our dev environement, take any live example and fix it from there (or use npm run dev, it's a live reload jest unit test env).\n\nWe currently do not have an npm run build:watch so maybe that's what you would require? So that you could just:\n- clone v2 branch of instantsearch.js\n- yarn\n- npm link\n- npm run build:watch\n\nThen in your project:\n- npm link react-instantsearch\n\nWould that work for you?\n",
